{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Prompt for Shopify AI Developer
    
    Create a 100% visually and functionally identical FAQ / Accordion section based on this reference page:
    https://www.forhers.com/labs/frequently-asked-questions
    
    Layout Structure
    
    The section must replicate the two-column layout exactly like the reference.
    
    Left Column
    
    Large heading: “Process”
    
    Very large typography (clean, modern, bold)
    
    Aligned to the top-left
    
    Large empty space below the heading just like the reference
    
    This column mainly acts as a visual title block
    
    Right Column
    
    Contains the FAQ accordion list
    
    Each FAQ item has:
    
    Question text
    
    Expand/collapse arrow icon on the right
    
    Hidden answer content that expands when clicked
    
    Accordion Behavior
    
    Only one FAQ item open at a time
    
    Clicking another item closes the previous one
    
    Smooth expand/collapse animation
    
    Arrow icon rotates when opened
    
    Divider lines between FAQ items
    
    Clean minimal style
    
    Typography
    
    Modern sans-serif font
    
    Question text slightly bold
    
    Answer text lighter with comfortable line spacing
    
    Good readability on all devices
    
    Spacing
    
    Large vertical padding (top and bottom)
    
    Proper spacing between FAQ rows
    
    Balanced whitespace similar to the reference design
    
    Background Customization (Important)
    
    Make the entire section background fully editable in Shopify Theme Editor.
    
    Add settings that allow me to choose:
    
    Solid color background
    
    Gradient background
    
    Image background
    
    Settings required:
    
    Background color picker
    
    Gradient color controls
    
    Background image upload
    
    Image position control
    
    Image overlay opacity
    
    Background size (cover / contain)
    
    Shopify Customization Settings
    
    Inside the theme editor I should be able to:
    
    Add unlimited FAQ items
    
    Edit question text
    
    Edit answer text
    
    Reorder FAQ items
    
    Set which FAQ is open by default
    
    Adjust section padding
    
    Adjust max width
    
    Responsiveness
    
    The section must be fully responsive on all screen sizes including:
    
    Mobile phones
    
    Tablets
    
    Laptops
    
    Desktop monitors
    
    Ultra-wide screens
    
    Smart TVs
    
    Responsive behavior:
    
    Desktop
    
    Two column layout (title left / FAQ right)
    
    Tablet
    
    Slightly reduced spacing
    
    Columns still visible if space allows
    
    Mobile
    
    Layout stacks vertically
    
    “Process” heading on top
    
    FAQ accordion below
    
    Performance
    
    Lightweight code
    
    No unnecessary libraries
    
    Smooth animations
    
    Optimized for fast loading
    
    Accessibility
    
    Keyboard navigation support
    
    ARIA labels for accordion
    
    Proper semantic HTML
    
    Code Requirements
    
    Implement as a Shopify section (.liquid)
    
    Use schema settings for customization
    
    Clean and maintainable code
    
    Compatible with Online Store 2.0
    
    Visual Goal
    
    The final result must look almost identical to the reference page in terms of:
    
    layout
    
    spacing
    
    typography
    
    accordion behavior
    
    arrow animation
    
    minimal design style, Follow-Up Request – Glassmorphism FAQ Boxes Customization
    
    Please enhance the FAQ accordion section we discussed earlier with glassmorphism styling and advanced customization options.
    
    Glassmorphism Style for Question Boxes
    
    Each FAQ question container (the clickable box) should support a glassmorphism effect.
    
    The glass effect must include:
    
    Semi-transparent background
    
    Backdrop blur
    
    Soft border
    
    Subtle shadow
    
    Smooth hover effect
    
    Editable Glassmorphism Controls (Theme Editor)
    
    Add settings in the Shopify theme editor that allow me to control the glass effect dynamically:
    
    Glass Transparency
    
    Slider control (0% – 100%)
    
    Controls background opacity
    
    Blur Strength
    
    Slider (0px – 40px)
    
    Border Opacity
    
    Slider (0% – 100%)
    
    Border Color Picker
    
    Glass Background Color
    
    Color picker
    
    Shadow Intensity
    
    Slider for subtle depth
    
    Question Box Size Controls
    
    Allow full control over the size of each FAQ question box from the Shopify editor.
    
    Add settings for:
    
    Box Padding
    
    Top / Bottom padding slider
    
    Left / Right padding slider
    
    Box Width
    
    Adjustable max width
    
    Option for full width or contained width
    
    Border Radius
    
    Slider (0px – 40px)
    
    Spacing Between Questions
    
    Slider for vertical spacing
    
    Responsive Behavior
    
    Make sure the glassmorphism effect works perfectly across all devices:
    
    Mobile
    
    Tablet
    
    Laptop
    
    Desktop
    
    Ultra-wide screens
    
    TVs
    
    Blur effects should remain smooth and performant without lag.
    
    Visual Behavior
    
    When a question is:
    
    Closed: clean glass box with subtle border
    
    Hovered: slightly brighter glass effect
    
    Opened: box expands smoothly and arrow rotates
    
    Performance Requirement
    
    Use CSS backdrop-filter and optimized styles so the effect remains lightweight and fast.
    
    Goal
    
    The final design should combine:
    
    The minimal FAQ layout from the reference
    
    With modern glassmorphism FAQ boxes
    
    Fully customizable inside the Shopify Theme Editor, Additional Follow-Up – Glassmorphism Answer Container + Full Typography Control
    
    Please extend the FAQ section we discussed with the following improvements.
    
    Glassmorphism Container for the Answer
    
    Currently the glassmorphism effect is applied to the question box. I would like the answer content to also appear inside the same glassmorphism container when expanded.
    
    Behavior should be:
    
    When the question is closed
    
    Only the question box is visible.
    
    When the question is opened
    
    The container smoothly expands downward
    
    The answer appears inside the same glassmorphism box
    
    The glass panel grows naturally to contain both the question and the answer.
    
    This should look like one unified glass card expanding, not two separate elements.
    
    Glass Panel Behavior
    
    Smooth height expansion animation
    
    Maintain blur effect across the entire container
    
    Border and shadow remain consistent when expanded
    
    Text inside stays perfectly readable
    
    Typography Customization (Theme Editor)
    
    Add full font customization controls in the Shopify theme editor.
    
    Allow me to choose:
    
    Font Family
    
    Dropdown to select font for:
    
    Section title
    
    Questions
    
    Answers
    
    Font Size Controls
    
    Title font size
    
    Question font size
    
    Answer font size
    
    Font Weight
    
    Adjustable weight for:
    
    Title
    
    Questions
    
    Answers
    
    Letter Spacing
    
    Adjustable slider
    
    Line Height
    
    Adjustable slider for answer readability
    
    Text Color Controls
    
    Add color pickers for:
    
    Section title color
    
    Question text color
    
    Answer text color
    
    Icon / arrow color
    
    Additional Customization Controls
    
    Also ensure all previously requested controls remain available:
    
    Background type (image / gradient / solid color)
    
    Glassmorphism transparency %
    
    Blur strength
    
    Border opacity
    
    Border color
    
    Shadow intensity
    
    Box padding
    
    Box border radius
    
    Spacing between FAQ items
    
    Question box width / max width
    
    Responsiveness
    
    All typography and glass effects must automatically scale and remain readable on:
    
    Mobile phones
    
    Tablets
    
    Laptops
    
    Desktops
    
    Ultra-wide screens
    
    TVs
    
    Final Goal
    
    The FAQ section should behave like expanding glass cards where:
    
    Each question is a glass panel
    
    Opening the question reveals the answer inside the same panel
    
    Everything is fully customizable from the Shopify Theme Editor
{% enddoc %}
{% assign ai_gen_id = block.id | replace: '_', '' | downcase %}

{% style %}
  .ai-faq-section-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    padding: {{ block.settings.padding_top }}px 0 {{ block.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
    background-color: {{ block.settings.background_color }};
    {% if block.settings.background_gradient != blank %}
      background-image: {{ block.settings.background_gradient }};
    {% endif %}
    {% if block.settings.background_image %}
      background-image: url('{{ block.settings.background_image | image_url: width: 2000 }}');
      background-size: {{ block.settings.background_size }};
      background-position: {{ block.settings.background_position }};
      background-repeat: no-repeat;
    {% endif %}
    position: relative;
  }

  .ai-faq-section-{{ ai_gen_id }}::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, {{ block.settings.overlay_opacity | divided_by: 100.0 }});
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .ai-faq-container-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    max-width: {{ block.settings.max_width }}px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 20px;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .ai-faq-grid-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    gap: 80px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .ai-faq-title-column-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    position: sticky;
    top: 40px;
  }

  .ai-faq-main-heading-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-family: {{ block.settings.title_font.family }}, {{ block.settings.title_font.fallback_families }};
    font-weight: {{ block.settings.title_font.weight }};
    font-style: {{ block.settings.title_font.style }};
    font-size: {{ block.settings.title_size }}px;
    line-height: {{ block.settings.title_line_height }};
    letter-spacing: {{ block.settings.title_letter_spacing }}em;
    margin: 0;
    color: {{ block.settings.title_color }};
  }

  .ai-faq-accordion-column-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: {{ block.settings.question_spacing }}px;
  }

  .ai-faq-item-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    {% assign glass_bg_r = block.settings.glass_background | color_extract: 'red' %}
    {% assign glass_bg_g = block.settings.glass_background | color_extract: 'green' %}
    {% assign glass_bg_b = block.settings.glass_background | color_extract: 'blue' %}
    {% assign glass_opacity = block.settings.glass_transparency | divided_by: 100.0 %}
    
    background: rgba({{ glass_bg_r }}, {{ glass_bg_g }}, {{ glass_bg_b }}, {{ glass_opacity }});
    backdrop-filter: blur({{ block.settings.glass_blur }}px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur({{ block.settings.glass_blur }}px);
    border: 1px solid rgba({{ block.settings.glass_border | color_extract: 'red' }}, {{ block.settings.glass_border | color_extract: 'green' }}, {{ block.settings.glass_border | color_extract: 'blue' }}, {{ block.settings.glass_border_opacity | divided_by: 100.0 }});
    border-radius: {{ block.settings.glass_border_radius }}px;
    box-shadow: 0 {{ block.settings.glass_shadow_y }}px {{ block.settings.glass_shadow_blur }}px rgba(0, 0, 0, {{ block.settings.glass_shadow_opacity | divided_by: 100.0 }});
    transition: all 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
    overflow: hidden;
    {% if block.settings.box_max_width_enabled %}
      max-width: {{ block.settings.box_max_width }}px;
    {% else %}
      width: 100%;
    {% endif %}
  }

  .ai-faq-item-{{ ai_gen_id }}:hover {
    {% assign hover_opacity = glass_opacity | plus: 0.1 %}
    {% if hover_opacity > 1 %}
      {% assign hover_opacity = 1 %}
    {% endif %}
    background: rgba({{ glass_bg_r }}, {{ glass_bg_g }}, {{ glass_bg_b }}, {{ hover_opacity }});
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 {{ block.settings.glass_shadow_y | plus: 4 }}px {{ block.settings.glass_shadow_blur | plus: 8 }}px rgba(0, 0, 0, {{ block.settings.glass_shadow_opacity | divided_by: 100.0 | plus: 0.05 }});
  }

  .ai-faq-question-button-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: {{ block.settings.box_padding_vertical }}px {{ block.settings.box_padding_horizontal }}px;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .ai-faq-question-text-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-family: {{ block.settings.question_font.family }}, {{ block.settings.question_font.fallback_families }};
    font-weight: {{ block.settings.question_font.weight }};
    font-style: {{ block.settings.question_font.style }};
    font-size: {{ block.settings.question_size }}px;
    line-height: {{ block.settings.question_line_height }};
    letter-spacing: {{ block.settings.question_letter_spacing }}em;
    color: {{ block.settings.question_color }};
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ai-faq-icon-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
    color: {{ block.settings.icon_color }};
  }

  .ai-faq-item-{{ ai_gen_id }}.active .ai-faq-icon-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .ai-faq-answer-wrapper-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    --faq-answer-max-height: 0px;
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1), padding 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1), opacity 0.3s ease;
    opacity: 0;
  }

  .ai-faq-item-{{ ai_gen_id }}.active .ai-faq-answer-wrapper-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    max-height: var(--faq-answer-max-height);
    padding: 0 {{ block.settings.box_padding_horizontal }}px {{ block.settings.box_padding_vertical }}px;
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .ai-faq-answer-content-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    font-family: {{ block.settings.answer_font.family }}, {{ block.settings.answer_font.fallback_families }};
    font-weight: {{ block.settings.answer_font.weight }};
    font-style: {{ block.settings.answer_font.style }};
    font-size: {{ block.settings.answer_size }}px;
    line-height: {{ block.settings.answer_line_height }};
    letter-spacing: {{ block.settings.answer_letter_spacing }}em;
    color: {{ block.settings.answer_color }};
    padding-right: 44px;
  }

  .ai-faq-answer-content-{{ ai_gen_id }} p {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }

  .ai-faq-answer-content-{{ ai_gen_id }} p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 989px) {
    .ai-faq-grid-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 40px;
    }

    .ai-faq-title-column-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      position: static;
    }

    .ai-faq-main-heading-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.title_size | times: 0.7 }}px;
    }

    .ai-faq-item-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      max-width: 100%;
    }
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 749px) {
    .ai-faq-section-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      padding: {{ block.settings.padding_top | times: 0.7 }}px 0 {{ block.settings.padding_bottom | times: 0.7 }}px;
    }

    .ai-faq-container-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      padding: 0 16px;
    }

    .ai-faq-grid-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      gap: 30px;
    }

    .ai-faq-accordion-column-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      gap: {{ block.settings.question_spacing | times: 0.8 }}px;
    }

    .ai-faq-main-heading-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.title_size | times: 0.6 }}px;
    }

    .ai-faq-question-text-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.question_size | times: 0.9 }}px;
    }

    .ai-faq-answer-content-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      font-size: {{ block.settings.answer_size | times: 0.9 }}px;
      padding-right: 0;
    }

    .ai-faq-question-button-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      padding: {{ block.settings.box_padding_vertical | times: 0.8 }}px {{ block.settings.box_padding_horizontal | times: 0.8 }}px;
    }

    .ai-faq-item-{{ ai_gen_id }}.active .ai-faq-answer-wrapper-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      padding: 0 {{ block.settings.box_padding_horizontal | times: 0.8 }}px {{ block.settings.box_padding_vertical | times: 0.8 }}px;
    }
  }

  @supports not (backdrop-filter: blur(10px)) {
    .ai-faq-item-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
      background: rgba({{ glass_bg_r }}, {{ glass_bg_g }}, {{ glass_bg_b }}, {{ glass_opacity | plus: 0.2 }});
    }
  }
{% endstyle %}

<faq-accordion-{{ ai_gen_id }} class="ai-faq-section-{{ ai_gen_id }}" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
  <div class="ai-faq-container-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
    <div class="ai-faq-grid-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
      <div class="ai-faq-title-column-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
        <h2 class="ai-faq-main-heading-{{ ai_gen_id }}">{{ block.settings.section_heading }}</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="ai-faq-accordion-column-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
        {% for i in (1..10) %}
          {% liquid
            assign question_key = 'question_' | append: i
            assign answer_key = 'answer_' | append: i
            assign open_key = 'open_' | append: i
            
            assign question = block.settings[question_key]
            assign answer = block.settings[answer_key]
            assign is_open = block.settings[open_key]
          %}

          {% if question != blank %}
            <div class="ai-faq-item-{{ ai_gen_id }} {% if is_open %}active{% endif %}" data-faq-item>
              <button
                class="ai-faq-question-button-{{ ai_gen_id }}"
                aria-expanded="{% if is_open %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}"
                data-faq-button
              >
                <h3 class="ai-faq-question-text-{{ ai_gen_id }}">{{ question }}</h3>
                <svg class="ai-faq-icon-{{ ai_gen_id }}" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                  <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
                </svg>
              </button>
              <div class="ai-faq-answer-wrapper-{{ ai_gen_id }}" data-faq-answer>
                <div class="ai-faq-answer-content-{{ ai_gen_id }}">
                  {{ answer }}
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</faq-accordion-{{ ai_gen_id }}>

<script>
  (function() {
    class FaqAccordion{{ ai_gen_id }} extends HTMLElement {
      constructor() {
        super();
        this.handleResize = () => this.syncAnswerHeights();
      }

      connectedCallback() {
        this.items = this.querySelectorAll('[data-faq-item]');
        this.setupEventListeners();
        this.syncAnswerHeights();
        window.addEventListener('resize', this.handleResize);
      }

      setupEventListeners() {
        this.items.forEach((item) => {
          const button = item.querySelector('[data-faq-button]');
          
          button.addEventListener('click', () => {
            const isActive = item.classList.contains('active');
            
            this.items.forEach((otherItem) => {
              if (otherItem !== item) {
                otherItem.classList.remove('active');
                const otherButton = otherItem.querySelector('[data-faq-button]');
                otherButton.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
                this.updateAnswerHeight(otherItem);
              }
            });
            
            if (isActive) {
              item.classList.remove('active');
              button.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
              this.updateAnswerHeight(item);
            } else {
              item.classList.add('active');
              button.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
              this.updateAnswerHeight(item);
            }
          });

          button.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
            if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
              e.preventDefault();
              button.click();
            }
          });
        });
      }

      updateAnswerHeight(item) {
        const answer = item.querySelector('[data-faq-answer]');
        if (!answer) return;

        if (item.classList.contains('active')) {
          answer.style.setProperty('--faq-answer-max-height', `${answer.scrollHeight}px`);
        } else {
          answer.style.setProperty('--faq-answer-max-height', '0px');
        }
      }

      syncAnswerHeights() {
        this.items.forEach((item) => this.updateAnswerHeight(item));
      }

      disconnectedCallback() {
        window.removeEventListener('resize', this.handleResize);
      }
    }

    customElements.define('faq-accordion-{{ ai_gen_id }}', FaqAccordion{{ ai_gen_id }});
  })();
</script>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "FAQ accordion",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Layout"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "section_heading",
      "label": "Section heading",
      "default": "Process"
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "max_width",
      "label": "Maximum width",
      "min": 800,
      "max": 1600,
      "step": 100,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 1200
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_top",
      "label": "Top padding",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 10,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 100
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_bottom",
      "label": "Bottom padding",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 200,
      "step": 10,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 100
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Background"
    },
    {
      "type": "color",
      "id": "background_color",
      "label": "Background color",
      "default": "#ffffff"
    },
    {
      "type": "color_background",
      "id": "background_gradient",
      "label": "Background gradient"
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "background_image",
      "label": "Background image"
    },
    {
      "type": "select",
      "id": "background_size",
      "label": "Background size",
      "options": [
        {
          "value": "cover",
          "label": "Cover"
        },
        {
          "value": "contain",
          "label": "Contain"
        },
        {
          "value": "auto",
          "label": "Auto"
        }
      ],
      "default": "cover"
    },
    {
      "type": "select",
      "id": "background_position",
      "label": "Background position",
      "options": [
        {
          "value": "center",
          "label": "Center"
        },
        {
          "value": "top",
          "label": "Top"
        },
        {
          "value": "bottom",
          "label": "Bottom"
        },
        {
          "value": "left",
          "label": "Left"
        },
        {
          "value": "right",
          "label": "Right"
        }
      ],
